## Introduction

This draft reports the output of an automated natural-experiment discovery run. The
method lineage is LoRD3: the local regression-discontinuity discovery scan of Herlands,
McFowland III, Wilson & Neill (2018, KDD), extended in Herlands (2019, CMU thesis) to
the subset-scan difference-in-differences design (SuDDDS, ch. 6), and connected to
downstream effect estimation by Jakubowski, Somanchi, McFowland III & Neill (2023).
The pipeline fits a smooth treatment model, scans local neighborhoods (rdd) or
covariate-subset/time configurations (did) for treatment-assignment discontinuities,
validates each discovery with a falsification battery, and only then estimates effects.

